===Noun===
'''bogey''' (''plural:'' '''[[bogeys]]''')
#{{golf}} A score of one over [[par]] in golf.
# One of two sets of wheels under a train car.
# (''British'') A piece of solid or [[semisolid]] [[mucus]] in or removed from the [[nostril]].
# (''Engineering'') A representative specimin, taken from the centre a spread of production - a sample with bogey (typical) characteristics.
